r><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uvdayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vdayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/24/01 3:48:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/shadowdragon77/guildoffice/Vdayan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: class........</span><hr size=1> Uhmm . . what is the best class?   I think that is truly an individual preference as to what people like to do and play as far as abilities.<br>
<br>
I play several different classes and each have individual value and enjoyment.   Depends on what you like to do.<br>
<br>
My main is a bard, but I also really like my rogue so it is why I started this site.  I have a cleric as well, and I like him because I take pride in keeping a party alive.  I get a lot of satisfaction out of that.   My rogue is actually roleplayed as a spy.  I like sneaking and hiding where others cannot go.  The bard rocks cause he adds so much to everything all around and helps a party immensely.<br>
<br>
I am sure other classes are fun to play too.  Each has their own merits.<br>
<br>
If leveling is your goal then pick a human, non hybrid class as they have no experience penalties.  I personally could care less about leveling as fast as I can as my enjoyment of the game comes from the classes I enjoy playing and my in game friends. <p>Warmest Regards,<br>
Vdayan Windrider, Bard of the 51st Song<br>
Co-Leader/Founder of <b> <a href="http://members.home.net/shadowdragon77/index.htm" target= "_blank"> Faydwer's Brethren</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Tetley</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/17/02 3:20:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> We have class</span><hr size=1> I have a Druid, Bard, Warrior, and Rogue. Its a toss up between Rogue and Druid for me. Both can get around the world on their own, although it takes a rogue a bit longer, but Rogues can go where others don't dare. For that reason I can solo a lot of quests, explore a lot of regons, and now it's even better as going to the Nexus means I dont have to get a boat everywhere.<br>
My only gripe is that it's hard to find groups, others dont appreciate what rogues can do, some even prefer monks in their party!!!! I'm sure that if i didnt want to give out much damage and not be able to pull MOB's off casters I would choose a monk ). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uspidor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spidor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/waterchaos.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/27/02 3:50:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidorluc.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have class</span><hr size=1> Best class? Define 'Best.'<br>
